<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Potential buffer over-read of stream->stream_name: strcmp(stream->stream_name, old) reads byte-by-byte until a '\0' is found. If stream->stream_name is not guaranteed to contain a terminating NUL within its OS_MAX_PATH_LEN bytes (for example, if the record was initialized/updated elsewhere using memcpy or an unterminated strncpy, or the entry is uninitialized/corrupted), strcmp can read past the bounds of stream->stream_name and thus violate Rule 21.17. (Note: the 'old' argument is validated earlier by OS_TranslatePath when OS_rename proceeds, so the risk is the stream->stream_name side.)
</scenario>
